  <TR><TD ALIGN="left" WIDTH="150">Here we have the same stockholders<BR ALIGN='left'/>owning the old and the new company. We<BR ALIGN='left'/>have the same assets. We have the same<BR ALIGN='left'/>liabilities except for the scaled down<BR ALIGN='left'/>demands of common creditors. And even as<BR ALIGN='left'/>to these the new corporation agreed that<BR ALIGN='left'/>if it failed to pay the installment<BR ALIGN='left'/>parts of their respective debts the<BR ALIGN='left'/>common creditors were free to advance<BR ALIGN='left'/>claims for the full amounts owing should<BR ALIGN='left'/>there be a subsequent bankruptcy.</TD></TR>
